---
// ProfileCard — image left, text right. Stacks on mobile.
---

<div class="rounded-2xl border border-border dark:border-dark-border bg-surface dark:bg-dark-surface p-8 sm:p-10 fade-in">
  <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-8 sm:gap-10 items-center sm:items-start">

    <!-- Photo -->
    <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-full sm:w-72 lg:w-80">
      <img
        src="/assets/profile.jpg"
        alt="Photo of Justin Park"
        width="320"
        height="320"
        class="w-full sm:w-72 lg:w-80 aspect-square object-cover rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary/30 dark:border-dark-primary/30 shadow-md"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Text -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 text-center sm:text-left">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-text dark:text-dark-text leading-tight">
          Justin Park
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg font-medium text-primary dark:text-dark-primary mt-1">
          Software Engineer
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-text-muted dark:text-dark-text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-prose">
        I build developer tools and AI-assisted products — software that makes technical work
        faster, more reliable, and easier to reason about. Currently I'm an Engineering &amp;
        Implementations Intern at Facilitron, shipping automation tooling that cuts
        implementation time in half. I led frontend development on OTTER, an open-source
        desktop app built with an eight-person team as our senior capstone. I'm drawn to the
        full arc of a product: the problem, the tradeoffs, and shipping something that holds up.
      </p>

    </div>

  </div>
</div>
